[The nationwide epidemic in 2011 was a result of feeding contaminated feed to the dairy cows during the monsoon; see: A Fasanella, G Garofolo, MJ Hossain, M Shamsuddin, JK Blackburn, M Hugh-Jones. Bangladesh anthrax outbreaks are probably caused by contaminated livestock feed http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=8644675.

This recent outbreak in Sirajganj is before the monsoon season and therefore livestock would have been grazing. But Sirajganj has a clay soil and enzootic anthrax is not reported for such areas. So it will be interesting to see what the veterinary services find as to the cause of this outbreak. So far only the public health response has been reported. - Mod.MHJ

Maps of Bangladesh can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/5Tur and http://tinyurl.com/bw2fuve. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
